================================================================================
PERFORMANCE ISSUES (Priority Order)
================================================================================

P0 — SLOW SERVER RESPONSE TIME (all pages)
───────────────────────────────────────────
Root cause: Edge runtime + Turbopack dev server overhead. Pages with server-side
DB queries pay high TTFB. Homepage saw 6,660 ms document latency; Hypothesis
3,750 ms; Arena 5,160 ms; Explore 820 ms.

RCA:
- Homepage (`src/app/page.tsx`): getHomeData() runs 5+ sequential DB queries
  including a Promise.all that does N+1 queries (one per problem statement to
  fetch its datasets). Lines 93-113 — N+1 waterfall.
- Hypothesis (`src/app/hypothesis/[id]/layout.tsx`): getHypothesisData() called
  TWICE — once for generateMetadata (line 26) and once for HypothesisLayout
  (line 89). No deduplication/caching between them.
- Arena (`src/app/arena/page.tsx`): Entire page is "use client" — no SSR.
  Initial HTML is empty shell. All data loaded client-side via useEffect (3
  API calls: getMatchup, getArenaRankings, getStarsBatch).

Actions:
  [ ] Fix N+1 in Homepage: batch dataset lookup with a single JOIN instead of
      Promise.all + per-PS query (src/app/page.tsx:93-113)
  [ ] Deduplicate getHypothesisData() in hypothesis layout — use React cache()
      or unstable_cache so generateMetadata + layout share one DB call
      (src/app/hypothesis/[id]/layout.tsx)
  [ ] Consider converting Arena to server component for initial rankings load
      (or at least SSR the leaderboard table)

P1 — LARGE CONTENTFUL PAINT (LCP) — ALL PAGES
──────────────────────────────────────────────
Measured: Homepage 7.1s, Explore 3.4s, Hypothesis 7.4s, Arena 6.9s

RCA:
- LCP element on most pages is text (h1 or hypothesis statement). LCP is
  blocked by: (1) slow document response (see P0), (2) render-blocking JS,
  (3) client-only pages that render nothing until JS hydrates + fetches data.
- Hypothesis page is entirely "use client" — shows a spinner until the API
  call completes. Zero server-rendered content. LCP = time until JS fetches
  data and renders.
- Arena page — same problem. 100% client rendered.

Actions:
  [ ] Convert hypothesis detail page to server component (SSR the main
      hypothesis data, keep interactive parts as client islands)
      (src/app/hypothesis/[id]/page.tsx — entire file is "use client")
  [ ] At minimum, SSR the hypothesis statement + rationale + metadata to
      eliminate the loading spinner as LCP

P2 — UNUSED / UNMINIFIED JAVASCRIPT (all pages)
────────────────────────────────────────────────
Measured: ~493 KiB unused JS (homepage), ~275 KiB (other pages), ~174 KiB
unminified JS.

RCA:
- Dev server (Turbopack) doesn't minify or tree-shake — this will largely
  resolve in production build.
- However: lucide-react icons are imported individually across many components
  but there's no guarantee the bundler tree-shakes all unused exports.
- Large client bundles: react-dom, next-devtools (dev only), client runtime.

Actions:
  [ ] Verify production build (`next build`) JS bundle sizes — most of this
      is dev-only overhead from Turbopack
  [ ] Consider dynamic imports for heavy client-only sections (arena page,
      hypothesis detail tabs) to reduce initial bundle
  [ ] Audit lucide-react — ensure only individual icon imports (already done)

P3 — TOTAL BLOCKING TIME (TBT) & TIME TO INTERACTIVE (TTI)
───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Measured: TBT 210-510ms, TTI 6.9-7.3s across pages.

RCA:
- Heavy JS execution during hydration. Explore page had 1.3s of JS execution.
- "use client" pages (Arena, Hypothesis detail) must download, parse, and
  execute all JS before becoming interactive.
- Multiple useEffect hooks fire on mount, triggering additional API fetches
  (stars batch, matchup, rankings) that block meaningful interaction.

Actions:
  [ ] Reduce client JS by SSR-ing data (see P1)
  [ ] Lazy-load non-critical client components (share menus, star batch
      fetching) — defer star loading to after initial paint

P4 — CUMULATIVE LAYOUT SHIFT (CLS) — Arena page
─────────────────────────────────────────────────
Measured: Arena CLS = 0.321 (POOR, threshold is 0.1)

RCA:
- Arena page renders empty shell, then matchup cards pop in after API response.
  The entire matchup section shifts the layout.
- No skeleton/placeholder dimensions reserved for the matchup grid.

Actions:
  [ ] Add min-height or skeleton placeholders for the Arena matchup section
      so content doesn't shift when data loads (src/app/arena/page.tsx:251-400)
  [ ] Set explicit dimensions on the vote button area

P5 — LEGACY JAVASCRIPT (all pages)
───────────────────────────────────
Measured: ~8 KiB savings possible.

RCA:
- Some legacy JS patterns detected (likely from dependencies, not app code).
- Minor in production. Will be addressed by build toolchain.

Actions:
  [ ] Verify in production build. Low priority.

================================================================================
ACCESSIBILITY ISSUES
================================================================================

A1 — COLOR CONTRAST RATIO (Arena + Hypothesis pages)
─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Score: Arena 96, Hypothesis 96 (both fail contrast)

Failing elements (common pattern): `text-stone-300` and `text-stone-400` on
white backgrounds. These colors have insufficient contrast ratio (< 4.5:1 for
normal text, < 3:1 for large text).

Specific violators:

Arena page (src/app/arena/page.tsx):
  - Line 42: "Hypothesis A/B" label — `text-stone-300` (extremely low contrast)
  - Line 67-68: Star/Share buttons — `text-stone-400`
  - Line 276: "vs" text — `text-stone-300`
  - Line 406: "completed only" — `text-stone-400`
  - Line 412-419: Table headers — `text-stone-400`
  - Line 247: Subtitle — `text-stone-400`

Hypothesis page (src/app/hypothesis/[id]/page.tsx):
  - Line 241: "Source hidden" text — `text-stone-400`
  - Line 277: BibTeX "COPY" button — `text-stone-400`
  - Comment timestamps — `text-stone-400`
  - Reply buttons — `text-stone-400`
  - "No citations" italic — `text-stone-400`

Actions:
  [ ] Replace `text-stone-300` with `text-stone-500` (or darker) for all
      text elements on white backgrounds
  [ ] Replace `text-stone-400` with `text-stone-500` for small/body text
      to meet WCAG AA 4.5:1 ratio
  [ ] Specifically fix: Arena card labels, Arena "vs", table headers,
      hypothesis "Source hidden", comment timestamps, reply buttons

